In 2010, BiodentineTM (Septodont; France), a quicker setting calcium silicate-based restorative cement, was introduced to the market. This cement was developed as a dentine replacement material, with a novel clinical application for this family of materials, with the intention that it would function as a direct coronal restoration. The comparatively short working/setting time (approximately 12 minutes) enables the use of this cement for clinical restorative procedures, which would be impossible with modern MTAs that achieve only an initial set within 3-4 hours.
